body:
Here's a fragment showing how to use the Expression builder APIs to created a filter with a constant list, yielding the same query as before. This issue would provide a nicer way to do the same thing without all the Expression builder APIs.

```c#
var ids = new[] { 1, 2, 3 };

// Default behavior: parameterized with OPENJSON:
// WHERE [b].[Id] IN (SELECT [i].[value] FROM OPENJSON(@__ids_0) WITH ([value] int '$') AS [i])
_ = await ctx.Blogs.Where(b => ids.Contains(b.Id)).ToListAsync();

// With constant node:
// WHERE [b].[Id] IN (1, 2, 3)
var containsMethod = typeof(Enumerable).GetMethods()
    .Single(m => m.Name == nameof(Enumerable.Contains) && m.GetParameters().Length == 2);

var blogParam = Expression.Parameter(typeof(Blog), "b");
var filter = Expression.Lambda<Func<Blog, bool>>(
    Expression.Call(
        containsMethod.MakeGenericMethod(typeof(int)),
        Expression.Constant(ids),
        Expression.Property(blogParam, nameof(Blog.Id))),
    blogParam);

_ = await ctx.Blogs.Where(filter).ToListAsync();
```
